This paper discusses the use of GANs for numeric data generation and proposes constrained network structures for WGANs. The paper focuses on evaluating the performance of these structures in data augmentation and improving the generation of structured data. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.CV (Computer Vision). Additionally, the paper mentions the strong correlations between features of numeric data, indicating a possible focus on neural networks, making cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) a likely sub-category. Finally, the paper evaluates the performance of the proposed structures on datasets, indicating a possible focus on data science, making cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) a likely sub-category as well.
